@startuml fig-proxy-arp
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Proxy ARP: Router Replies on Behalf of a Remote Host

participant "Host A\nLAN 1\nIP_A" as A #FFE0B2
participant "Router\nMAC_R" as R #E3F2FD
participant "Host B\nLAN 2\nIP_B" as B #C8E6C9

A -[#1565C0]> R : ARP Request (broadcast)\n"Who has IP_B?"

R -[#43A047]> A : ARP Reply (proxy)\n"IP_B is at MAC_R"

== Host A believes IP_B lives at MAC_R ==

A -> R : Ethernet frame dst=MAC_R\n(carrying IP packet for IP_B)
R -> B : Router forwards to LAN 2\n(new Ethernet frame dst=MAC_B)

legend right
  Host B is on a different subnet.
  The router intercepts the ARP request
  and replies with its own MAC address.
  Host A sends frames to the router
  which then forwards them to Host B.
endlegend
@enduml
